==Estonian==
===Etymology===
Compound of kah- and -eksa. The former comes from [[kaks]], while the latter is from ann original *''deksa'', which is from an Iranian language, compare Kurdish [[deh]]. So the compound originally meant two (from) ten.
===Cardinal number===
